title: RY Crosses Above Key Moving Average Level - Nasdaq.com
text: In trading on Thursday, shares of Royal Bank of Canada (Montreal, Quebec) (Symbol: RY) crossed above their 200 day moving average of $76.11, changing hands as high as $76.48 per share. Royal Bank of Canada (Montreal, Quebec) shares are currently trading up about 1.6% on the day. The chart below shows the one year performance of RY shares, versus its 200 day moving average:     Looking at the chart above, RY's low point in its 52 week range is $65.76 per share, with $81.56 as the 52 week high point - that compares with a last trade of $76.25.
